reporting-org.narrative: The federal government of the United States

description.narrative: Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation – the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.

This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes GENERAL SERVICES [Covers contractual services covering personal services, supplies, and material when such services are not otherwise classified. Includes contract secretaries and other contract personnel required for ITA events and projects. Includes IBC contract personnel with equipment and supplies, and FAS contracts and agreements for technical assistance, secretaries, and foreign nationals; research, projects, and public relations contracts for sponsored events.]. Administrative action [Covers contractual services covering personal services, supplies, and material when such services are not otherwise classified. Includes contract secretaries and other contract personnel required for ITA events and projects. Includes IBC contract personnel with equipment and supplies, and FAS contracts and agreements for technical assistance, secretaries, and foreign nationals; research, projects, and public relations contracts for sponsored events.].
